<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="518" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,716,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,716,742]" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Metope wide, often smooth and without carinae. Coryphe transverse. Forewings wide, with wide hypocostal plate. Hind wings rudimentary. Abdominal sternites IV–VI in imago each with two large sensory pits medially. Phallobase strongly curved, its proximal part (basement) with a pair of lobe-shaped processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,716,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,533,824,850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Supplementary description.</emphasis>
Eyes large, 0.5 as wide as coryphe (in dorsal view). Coryphe transverse, with lateral margins weakly diverging anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[658,730,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1230,1254]" captionTargetBox="[152,1417,201,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-334@3.[151,1435,179,1239]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Mékalis. 1—dorsal view; 2—lateral view; 3—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[745,761,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1420,678,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-251@5.[151,1435,669,1717]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 6–8. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), female, Aïn Kerma. 6—dorsal view; 7—lateral view; 8—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[775,791,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[805,835,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[161,1406,181,1236]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1266]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., 12–14—holotype, 15—female paratype, Marrakech. 12—dorsal view; 13, 15—lateral view; 14—frontal view.Abbreviation: kp — knee prominence. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[848,878,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[892,922,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1302,1326]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,159,1271]" captionTargetId="figure-314@9.[151,1436,151,1278]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Aïn Sefra. 20—face; 21—head and pronotum, dorsal view; 22—hind wing. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">21</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[935,965,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–31" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[167,1422,166,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-37@11.[151,1436,151,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 30–31. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), male, Aïn Kerma. 30 – face; 31 – head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[979,1010,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–40" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,209,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[195,1393,199,1876]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 39–40. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 39—face; 40—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1022,1054,860,887]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,191,1534]" captionTargetId="figure-28@16.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 53–55. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 53—face; 54—eye, scapus, pedicel, and paranotal lobe, frontal view; 55—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">55</figureCitation>
). Metope wide, often smooth and without carinae (
<figureCitation box="[342,416,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1230,1254]" captionTargetBox="[152,1417,201,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-334@3.[151,1435,179,1239]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Mékalis. 1—dorsal view; 2—lateral view; 3—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[430,445,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1420,678,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-251@5.[151,1435,669,1717]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 6–8. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), female, Aïn Kerma. 6—dorsal view; 7—lateral view; 8—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[460,489,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[502,532,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[161,1406,181,1236]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1266]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., 12–14—holotype, 15—female paratype, Marrakech. 12—dorsal view; 13, 15—lateral view; 14—frontal view.Abbreviation: kp — knee prominence. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[546,577,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1302,1326]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,159,1271]" captionTargetId="figure-314@9.[151,1436,151,1278]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Aïn Sefra. 20—face; 21—head and pronotum, dorsal view; 22—hind wing. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[589,619,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–31" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[167,1422,166,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-37@11.[151,1436,151,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 30–31. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), male, Aïn Kerma. 30 – face; 31 – head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">30</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[633,665,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–40" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,209,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[195,1393,199,1876]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 39–40. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 39—face; 40—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">39</figureCitation>
). Coryphe and metope joint at obtuse angle (in lateral view). Ocelli absent. Postclypeus smooth, without carinae. Rostrum reaching hind coxae; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1012,1026,932,946]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">rd</superScript>
segment narrowing apically, slightly shorter than 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[305,321,968,982]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">nd</superScript>
one. Pedicel globular. Pronotum with strongly convex anterior margin and nearly straight posterior margin. Paradiscal fields of pronotum wide behind the eyes. Paranotal lobes of pronotum wide, without carine, with slightly bent lower margin (
<figureCitation box="[516,600,1040,1067]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,191,1534]" captionTargetId="figure-28@16.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 53–55. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 53—face; 54—eye, scapus, pedicel, and paranotal lobe, frontal view; 55—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
). Forewings wide, extend beyond the abdomen apex, with weakly obtusely angulate costal margin and distinct membrane (
<figureCitation box="[677,749,1076,1102]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1230,1254]" captionTargetBox="[152,1417,201,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-334@3.[151,1435,179,1239]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Mékalis. 1—dorsal view; 2—lateral view; 3—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[760,776,1077,1103]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1420,678,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-251@5.[151,1435,669,1717]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 6–8. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), female, Aïn Kerma. 6—dorsal view; 7—lateral view; 8—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[787,817,1076,1102]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[828,858,1076,1102]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[161,1406,181,1236]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1266]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., 12–14—holotype, 15—female paratype, Marrakech. 12—dorsal view; 13, 15—lateral view; 14—frontal view.Abbreviation: kp — knee prominence. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[870,901,1076,1102]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">17</figureCitation>
). Forewings often with distinct shoulder-shaped prominence (or knee prominence) well recognized as bulge at first furcation of radius (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1201,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[161,1406,181,1236]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1266]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., 12–14—holotype, 15—female paratype, Marrakech. 12—dorsal view; 13, 15—lateral view; 14—frontal view.Abbreviation: kp — knee prominence. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[1212,1238,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">kp</emphasis>
). Forewings with wide precostal area and wide hypocostal plate, basal cell small. Clavus long, ⅔ of wing length. Hind wings rudimentary, nearly reaching abdomen basement (
<figureCitation box="[660,742,1184,1210]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1302,1326]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,159,1271]" captionTargetId="figure-314@9.[151,1436,151,1278]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Aïn Sefra. 20—face; 21—head and pronotum, dorsal view; 22—hind wing. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
), matte. Hind tibia with 1–2 lateral spines. First metatarsomere short and wide, with two latero-apical and 6–7 intermediate spines in continuous row. Second metatarsomere equal in length to first one, but narrower, with only two latero-apical spines. Ventral surface of first and second metatarsomeres with long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,716,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">
Abdominal sternites IV–VI of imago each with two large sensory pits medially (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1202,1328,1355]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1590,1614]" captionTargetBox="[204,1363,237,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-46@4.[151,1435,237,1552]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–5. Lethierium spp. 4—L. reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male (Mékalis), ventral view (scale bar—1 mm); 5—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), female (Aïn Kerma), sternite VI, ventral view (out of scale)." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
). Each pit comprises of wide circle depression of the cuticle with a sensory hair in its centre arising from dark brown socket, laying nearly horizontally and directed to the rim of the depression at acute angle to the midline of the sternite. Besides these large sensory pits the sternites IV–VI have also several trichobothria, from three to seven on each side along its posterior margin, which are represented by long sensory hair (longer than surrounding setae) arising from dark brown socket vertically from the cuticle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,716,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">
Male pygofer elongate vertically, with weakly obtuse or nearly right upper angle and nearly straight hind margins (
<figureCitation box="[215,305,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1599,1623]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,185,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-28@10.[171,1415,181,1575]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23–29. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Aïn Sefra, male genitalia. 23—pygofer, lateral view; 24—anal tube, dorsal view; 25—anal tube, lateral view; 26—penis and connective, lateral view; 27—penis, ventral view; 28—style, dorsal view; 29—style, lateral view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[319,349,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–38" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1482,1506]" captionTargetBox="[174,1429,254,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-250@12.[151,1436,224,1437]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 32–38. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, male genitalia. 32 – pygofer, lateral view; 33 – penis, ven- tral view; 34 – penis and connective, lateral view; 35 – style, lateral view; 36 – style, dorsal view; 37 – anal tube, dorsal view; 38 – anal tube, lateral view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">32</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[364,394,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">41</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[408,438,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">47</figureCitation>
, 
