<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,716,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="518">
Hind margin of female sternite VII widely concave (in ventral view), with labial median process (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[230,402,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–70" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,187,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-28@18.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 64–70. Lethierium spp., female. 64—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 65—same, ventral view; 66—L. reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Mékalis, sternite VII, dorsal view; 67—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 68—same, ventral view; 69—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, anal tube, dorsal view; 70—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, sternite VII, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 64–68, 70</figureCitation>
). Gonoplacs convex, without carinae (
<figureCitation box="[830,917,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[929,960,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–77" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,189,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[151,1436,181,1685]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 71–77. Lethierium spp., ovipositor structure, 71–75—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, 76–77—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma. 71—anal tube and gonoplac, dorsal view; 72, 76—gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, lateral view; 73—same, ventral view; 74—gonapophysis VIII; 75—apex of endogonocoxal lobe; 77—basement of gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, caudal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">71</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxa VIII with weakly lobe-shaped hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[303,388,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–77" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,189,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[151,1436,181,1685]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 71–77. Lethierium spp., ovipositor structure, 71–75—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, 76–77—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma. 71—anal tube and gonoplac, dorsal view; 72, 76—gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, lateral view; 73—same, ventral view; 74—gonapophysis VIII; 75—apex of endogonocoxal lobe; 77—basement of gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, caudal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). Anterior connective lamina of gonapophysis VIII wide, with three teeth in apical group and 3–4 teeth in lateral group. Endogonocoxal process slightly furcating apically (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1095,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–77" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,189,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[151,1436,181,1685]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 71–77. Lethierium spp., ovipositor structure, 71–75—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, 76–77—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma. 71—anal tube and gonoplac, dorsal view; 72, 76—gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, lateral view; 73—same, ventral view; 74—gonapophysis VIII; 75—apex of endogonocoxal lobe; 77—basement of gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, caudal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). Posterior connective laminae of gonapophyses IX vertically elongate, with its distal parts curved at obtuse angle (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1330,1940,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–77" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,189,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[151,1436,181,1685]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 71–77. Lethierium spp., ovipositor structure, 71–75—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, 76–77—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma. 71—anal tube and gonoplac, dorsal view; 72, 76—gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, lateral view; 73—same, ventral view; 74—gonapophysis VIII; 75—apex of endogonocoxal lobe; 77—basement of gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, caudal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Figs 72, 73, 76, 77</figureCitation>
). Median field of the laminae two-lobed (
<figureCitation box="[506,590,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–77" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,189,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[151,1436,181,1685]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 71–77. Lethierium spp., ovipositor structure, 71–75—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, 76–77—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma. 71—anal tube and gonoplac, dorsal view; 72, 76—gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, lateral view; 73—same, ventral view; 74—gonapophysis VIII; 75—apex of endogonocoxal lobe; 77—basement of gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, caudal view. Out of scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="518">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
). Lateral fields of the laminae short. Gonospiculum bridge large.
</paragraph>
